@startuml
title Upload File to BlockChain or Cloud

participant "Client" as Client
participant "BnodeApi" as BnodeApi
database "BlockChain" as Blockchain
cloud "Cloud" as Cloud

note over Client #lightyellow 
Request: multipart-formdata\nfile (binary)\nprivatekey_wif (string) \npublic_key_hex (string)\non_chain (boolean)\nResponse:\ncode (int)\nfile_id (string)\nencrypt_hex (string, encrypt random index list to hex)\ntx_id_list (string of array)
end note 

activate Client
->> BnodeApi : uploadFile() {multipart/form-data}
deactivate Client


group 1.divid upload file.\n2.get divided file array.\n3.genarate random index array.\n4.devided file array is numbering random index.\n5.encrypt genarate random index array to string.\n6.save No.5 string in server.#white
  
    activate BnodeApi
    
        loop [divided file array]
            ->Blockchain++:[upload Divided File(Max 100kb)]\r[txId]\r[fileHash]
            
                alt [[onchain]] true
                
                    group calculate hash\rwrite on blockchain#White
                        
                        -->Blockchain ++:[[hash]][blockHeight][transactionID(txid)][timestamp(time_t)]
                        
                            opt if error then return false; end
                    
                    
                
        
         else[[!onchain]]false
            
             loop [divided file array]   
                 -->>Cloud +:+[upload Devidied File(max size config.json)]+[filename]+[filepath]  
                 
                     alt success
                         <--Cloud -:-true+path_to_file
                         
                             opt failture
                                 <-Cloud--failture message    
                     
             
         
     deactivate Blockchain
     
     
     
        
       
       --->>+Server:"saveNo.5 String"\n(encrypted_index_array_string)+client_publicKeyHex+(server_privateWIF)+(salt_8byte_random_value)
           
           alt save ok
               <--- Server- :"ok"+index_encrypted_filename_path+" "+random_salt_base64_str+"\n"+"sha256_hash_of_original_file_data_in_HEX_format"
               
                   opt failure case scenario where something goes wrong during saving process like disk full etc..then we need handle this situation properly by returning appropriate response back client side so they know what happened exactly why their request failed instead just saying 'error occurred' without any details about reason behind such errors which makes debugging much harder than necessary especially when dealing complex systems involving multiple components working together simultaneously across different layers abstraction levels within same application stack itself let alone entire ecosystem surrounding those apps too including third party services providers who might also play role here somehow indirectly through APIs exposed publicly available online somewhere out there world wide web network infrastructure connecting everything globally speaking generally anyway...but I digress slightly off topic now sorry my bad habit rambling sometimes gets better me unfortunately :( However rest assured dear reader/user/friend whoever you may be reading these words right moment time space continuum existence reality whatever term prefer use describe state being alive conscious aware self-aware sentient intelligent entity capable thinking reasoning learning adapting evolving growing changing transforming becoming more perfect version ourselves day after another until finally reach ultimate goal perfection enlightenment nirvana paradise heaven utopia dream come truth fact fiction myth legend story tale narrative account description representation depiction illustration portrayal characterization simulation emulation imitation reproduction replication duplication repetition iteration variation modification alteration adjustment adaptation transformation evolution revolution innovation invention discovery exploration investigation research study analysis synthesis evaluation assessment judgment decision making problem solving creativity imagination intuition inspi